724742f-b.text:
1. American Seaman's Friend Society, 505-507 West Street at the N.E. corner of Jane Street, opposite Pier 51, North River. The building was erected in 1907. Its hexagonal tower is an outstanding landmark. May 12, 1927. P. L. Sperr.

2. The same, two years later. March 8, 1929. P. L. Sperr.

720686f-a.text: Jane Street, east from West Street. In the mid and background appear, the New York Central Railroad and the Ninth Avenue Elevated, running respectively on Washington and Greenwich Street's [sic]. The latter is to be removed in the near future. The former is of recent construction and is a portion of the Railroad's contribution to the West Side Improvement Project, whereby their tracks and trains were removed from the regular street bed. May 12, 1940. P.L. Sperr
